display.text: Interviewer script: This clinic is participating in a study on home-based partner testing and counseling, in which couples will receive a home visit 1-2 weeks from now or 6 months after the woman delivers their baby. In order to know whether you are eligible to participate in the study, I would like to ask you some questions.  If you are eligible, I will tell you more about the study so you can decide whether or not you want to participate. If you agree, you will be giving verbal consent for us to ask you these questions and record your answers without recording your name.
Client agreed to be screened for eligibility?
Thank you for considering being screened for the study. This will in no way affect the care that you, your children, or your partner will receive at the antenatal clinic.
display.hint: Continue to next page to submit responses.

display.text: How old were you on your last birthday?
display.hint: If younger than 14 years old, client is ineligible. Screening will not continue.
If no, client is ineligible to be in the study. Screening will not continue.

display.text: Using LMP (and pregnancy wheel tool) and/or client's fundal height, enter the client's estimated gestational age in weeks.
What is your ethnic group background? Choose one:
What is the highest level of education you attended? Choose one:
How would you characterize your employment or occupation? Choose all that apply:
Are you currently in a relationship?
display.hint: If not currently in a relationship, client is ineligible but continue screening

display.text: How old was your partner on their last birthday?
display.hint: If study partner is younger than 18 years old, client is ineligible to be in the study; however, continue screening to capture responses to all questions

display.text: How many times have you been pregnant?
How many living children do you have?
Do you plan to live within 20 kilometers of this clinic from now until 9 months after you deliver?
display.hint: If no, client is ineligible; however, continue screening to capture responses to all questions

display.text: Have you been tested for HIV before?
What was the result of your last HIV test?
Client is INELIGIBLE for the following reasons:
display.hint: If client is eligible for study, review previous questions and responses

display.text: Thank you for your time in answering these questions. Based on some of the answers you gave, you are ineligible to be a part of the study. This in no way affects the care you will receive here at this clinic. Can I answer any questions you may have?

display.hint: If client is NOT eligible for study, review previous questions and responses.

display.text: Say: Thank you for your time in answering these questions. Based on the answers you gave, you are eligible to be a part of the study. Would you like to participate in the study?
display.hint: Read consent form with participant and go through written consent process.

display.text: Enter Client ID from randomization envelopes.
display.hint:
5 Digit ID, cannot include 0. 
ex: 12345

display.text: Open Randomization Envelope. What is the clientâ€™s randomization arm?
I understand you do not want to participate in this study. Could you let me know why you would not like to participate? Check all that apply:

Say: Thank you for letting me know why you do not want to participate. It is important for us to know why women may feel this way. This will in no way affect the care that you, your children, or your partner will receive at the clinic.
The screening is now complete, please go to the next page to finalize your responses.

display.text: Script 1: I am now going to ask questions about your pregnancy. We will do our best to keep your answers confidential. By providing honest answers, you may be able to help us understand the health issues in your community better.
How much did your baby weigh after birth? (Kg)
How much does your baby weigh now? (Kg)
Script 2: Now I would like to talk to you about your antenatal care for your recent pregnancy.
Specify the other person who assisted in delivering
Did you get a cesarean section?
Were there any complications during delivery?
display.hint: Explain and review options with client and select all that apply.

display.text: Script 3: Now I would like to talk to you about breastfeeding.
Did you ever breastfeed after this delivery?
For how long did you breastfeed this child?
display.hint: Weeks

display.text: Script 4: Now I would like to talk about your health and your childâ€™s health.
Were you tested for HIV between the time you were tested for the study and now?
display.hint: (i.e. after enrolling while at the clinic if you did not receive a home visit,  or after the home visit)

display.text: Where were you tested for HIV?
What was the result of your most recent HIV test?
Have you ever enrolled or registered into the HIV comprehensive care clinic (CCC)?
Do you know your CD4 test results?
What was the result of your most recent CD4 test?
display.hint: CD4 = ___ cells/mL

display.text: Were you prescribed medicine to manage your HIV infection or protect your child from HIV?
Were you prescribed AZT/ZDV during your pregnancy?
For how long were you prescribed ART treatment?
Are you currently taking ART treatment you were prescribed?
Did you receive a single dose of Nevirapine and/or a dose of AZT/ZDV + 3TC during labor?
display.hint: Select yes if any of these were received.

display.text: Were you given AZT/ZDV and 3TC to take during the next 7 days after delivery?
Was your child prescribed Nevirapine syrup for 6 weeks after delivery or until after breastfeeding (or in rare circumstances Lamivudine)?
Is your child currently taking Nevirapine syrup?
Sometimes it is difficult to make infants consume Nevirapine. Has the child missed any doses during the past 7 days?
Thank you for your time in answering these questions.

Now we will do the blood draw for the infantâ€™s HIV test. 
Please do pre-test counseling and draw blood from infant for filter paper sample.
